                                    Transformation 

What is transformation?

    - Does not execute immediatlely 
    - Return new dataframe 
    - Is lazily evalutated
    - Builds the DAG 


Narrow Tranformation 

Wide Transformation 


df.explain() 

df.rdd.todebugString() # RDD lineage view 

Transformation :

Projection :

    - select() 
        - select() is used to select specific coilumn from dataframe.

            df.select("column1","column2)

    - selectExpr()
        SelectExpr() allows you to write SQl expression inside select.
            - df.selectExpr("column","expression As alias)

            df_emp.selectExpr("name",CASE WHEN salary > 60000 THEN "High" ELSE "Medium" as salary_grade").show() 


    - withColumn() 
        - Add or replace a column 
            df.withColumn("new_column",expression)


            df.withColumn("tax",expression)
              .withColumn("test",expression)

    - withColumns() # spark3.4+ 

        - Add multiple column in one call

            df.withColumns(
            {
            "col1":Expression2,
            "col2":Expression2
            })


    - withColumnRenamed()
        Rename one Column 

        - df.withColumnRenamed("old_name","new_column")



    - toDF() 

        Rename all columns at once

            df.toDF("col1","col2","col3","col4")

            # Number of column name must match exactly 


    - drop() 

        - Remove column(S) from dataframe.

        df.drop("column name")

    - alias() 

        - Temporarily rename column or Dataframe (mainly used in joins)

        emp_df.select(col("salary").alias("emp_sal"))

        emp=emp_df.alias("e")



    functions 

    select()                        choose columns

    selectExpr()                    SQl style select

    withColumn()                    Add/replace column 

    withColumns()                   add multiple cols 

    withColumnRenamed()             rename one column 

    toDf()                          rename all columns 

    drop()                          remove column

    alias                           tempporary rename 



Project: 1   HR payroll project & Department COST report 

From employee + department datasets, crete a final reporting dataframe that contains:

    - Standatdized column names
    - cleaned/drived metrics (bonus,tax,net_salary)
    - slaary band (high,medium and low)
    - Join with department name
    - A final report with only reqired columns 

    emp_data=[
    (1,"Gaurav",30,5000,101),
    (),
    ()
    ]

    emp_col= ["emp_id","name","age","salary",dept_id"]

    dept_data=[
    (101,"HR")
    ()
    ()
    ]

    dept_col=["dept_id",dept_name"]

    Q1. toDF - Standadize all column names (wharehouse friendly) 

            emp_id,emp_name,emp_age.............


    Q2. withColumnRenamed() - rename one specific column 

        salary --> base_salary

    Q3. withColumn() - Add 1 drived column 

        bonus---> 10% of salary 

    Q4. withColumns() - Add multiple colums in one slot 

        tax and net_salary with expression 

        tax--> 0.2 of salary 
        net salary= base_Sal+bonus-tax

    Q5. selectExpr() create SQl style calculated column 

        salary_band using CASE 

    Q6. alais() - Use alias in join 

        e= emp_band.alias("e")
        d=dept_df.alaias("d")

        joined= e.join(d,col......)


    Q7. drop() - Remove duplicate join column 

        - After join you'll have two dept_id columns if you select both 

            d. dept_id 


    Q8. select() - FInal projection for reporting 

    
    Q9. Show - FInal output 




    
    




